# the ignorant person needs to be taught; the one who has doubts needs
~~to have things explained to him; the negligent person needs to be
~~reminded; and the one who wilfully persists in error needs to be warned.
~~it is not right to treat one who knows about a ruling and one who is
~~ignorant of it in the same manner when rebuking them. treating one who
~~does not know too harshly will only put him off and make him refuse to
~~follow your advice, unlike teaching him with wisdom and gentleness,
~~because an ignorant person simply does not realize that he is making a
~~mistake. it is as if he is saying to the one who is rebuking him: “why
~~don’t you teach me before you launch an attack on me?” PageV11P0025
