~~his intestines in the fire. he used to steal from the hujjaaj (pilgrims)
~~with his crooked stick. if they spotted him, he would say ‘this got
~~caught on my stick,’ and if they did not spot him, he would take
~~whatever he had stolen . . .” another of the worst forms of theft is
~~stealing from the public purse. some of those who do this say “we are
~~only doing what others do.” they do not realize that what they are doing
~~is effectively stealing from all the muslims, because the public purse
~~belongs to all the muslims. imitating those who do not fear allaah is no
~~excuse. some people steal from the wealth of the kuffaar on the grounds
~~that they are kuffaar, but this is wrong; the only kuffaar whose wealth
~~we are allowed to take away are those who are actively fighting the
~~muslims, which does not apply to every kaafir individual or company.
~~PageV23P0065
# another form of theft is pick-pocketing, stealing something from a
~~person’s pocket without him realizing. some thieves enter people’s
~~houses as visitors, and steal from them. some steal from their guests’
~~bags. some - including women - go into stores and hide things in their
~~pockets or under their clothing. some think that the theft of small or
~~cheap items is of little consequence, but the prophet (peace and
~~blessings of allaah be upon him) said: “allaah has cursed the thief who
~~steals an egg and has his hand cut off, and the thief who steals a rope
