~~your brother that he does not want to be said." he was asked, "what do
~~you think if what is said about him is true?" he said, "if what you say
~~about him is true, this is backbiting, and if what you say about him is
~~not true, this is a lie." (reported by muslim, 4/2001). gossip or
~~backbiting means saying something about a muslim which may be true but
~~which he does not like to hear spoken, whether it be about his physical
~~appearance, his adherence to religion, his worldly affairs, his self,
~~his behaviour or his character. there are many forms of gossip,
