# harming a neighbour may take many forms, including: not allowing him
~~to fix a piece of wood to a shared wall or fence; expanding one's
~~dwelling in such a way as to deprive him of sun or air without his
~~permission; opening windows overlooking his house and looking out of
~~them to invade his privacy; disturbing him with loud sounds such as
~~hammering or shouting, especially when he is asleep or resting; or
~~throwing trash in front of his door. the sin of such deeds is increased
