~~heart.” after knowing this, if a muslim laughs to excess it is as if he
~~is undertaking a journey that he knows will lead to his doom. this is
~~the theoretical response to this problem, in brief. before we turn to
~~the practical aspects, we must point out that laughter is not haraam,
~~and the muslim is not expected to be dour-faced and stern and rigid.
~~laughter is something which is quite natural, and indeed allaah says in
~~the qur’aan (interpretation of the meaning): “and … it is he (allaah)
