~~say, “ya hayyu ya qayyoom, bi rahmatika astagheeth. allaahu rabbee wa la
~~ushriku bihi shay’an (o ever-living, o eternal one, by your mercy i seek
~~your help. allaah is my lord, and i do not associate anything with
~~him).” (saheeh al-jaami’, 4791). in the famous du’aa’ to relieve stress
~~and anxiety, he said: “allaahumma inni ‘abduka, wa’bnu ‘adbdika wa’bnu
~~amatika… (o allaah, i am your slave, the son of your slave, the son of
~~your maidservant…).” this is a concept which has to be understood
~~properly before we move on to a discussion of the practical ways of
~~dealing with the problem of excessive laughter, which can be dealt with
~~in the following ways: remembering death, the grave, the last day and
~~its reckoning, the bridge over hell (al-siraat), the fire, and all the
~~other terrors of the hereafter. the way to remember all these things is
~~to read the texts that describe these scenes and to study the details
~~and commentaries, as well as sitting with people who are ascetic
~~(zaahid) and whose hearts are devoted to allaah. PageV25P0018
# thinking about the situation of the muslims and how they are suffering
