# knowing that suppressing anger is one of the signs of taqwa (piety).
~~allaah has praised certain people in his book, and the prophet (peace
~~and blessings of allaah be upon him) highly commended them. there have
~~been prepared for them gardens as wide as the heavens and the earth. one
~~of their characteristics is that they “… spend (in allaah’s cause) in
~~prosperity and in adversity, [they] repress anger, and pardon men;
~~verily, allaah loves al-muhsinoon (the good-doers)” [aal ‘imraan 3:134 –
~~interpretation of the meaning]. these are the people whose good
~~qualities allaah has mentioned, people whom others admire and want to
~~catch up with. another of their characteristics is that “when they are
~~angry, they forgive” [al-shoora 42:37 – interpretation of the meaning].
~~paying attention when one is reminded. anger is something natural, with
~~regard to which people differ. it may be very hard for a person not to
~~get angry, but a sincere person, if he becomes angry and is reminded
