# even his fellow-prisoners, whom imaam ahmad used to lead in prayer in
~~chains, had a role to play in helping him to stand firm. one day when he
~~was in prison, imaam ahmad said, “i don’t care about being in prison –
~~it is no different from my home – or about being killed by the sword,
~~but i am afraid of the trial of being whipped.” one of the other
~~prisoners heard him and said, “don’t worry, o abu ‘abd-allaah, it is
~~only two lashes of the whip, then you don’t feel where the rest fall.”
