~~position, then do as the imaam is doing.’” (sunan al-tirmidhi, 591; see
~~also saheeh sunan al-tirmidhi, 484). also, there is the general meaning
~~of the hadeeth: “whatever you catch up with, pray.” not hastening unduly
~~to join a prayer in progress if the prayer starts and a person is still
~~on his way to the mosque, he should not hasten unduly; he should walk
~~with calmness and dignity, as indicated in the hadeeth of abu hurayrah
~~(may allaah be pleased with him): “the prophet (peace and blessings of
~~allaah be upon him) said: ‘if the prayer starts, do not approach it
~~running; approach it walking with calmness and dignity. whatever you
