# so, if a person has performed the rukoo’ of the second rak‘ah when the
~~iqaamah is called, then he should complete his prayer. if the iqaamah is
~~called before he does the rukoo’ of the second rak’ah, then he should
~~discontinue because what is left of sujood and tashahhud is not needed
~~any more. moreover, he should break without salaam, and it is enough to
~~have the intention in the heart, contrary to common misconception. being
~~informed of the correct direction of the qiblah whilst praying if there
