~~al-asqa’ (may allaah be pleased with him) that the prophet (peace and
~~blessings of allaah be upon him) said: “laylat al-qadr is a bright
~~night, neither hot nor cold, in which no meteors are seen.” (narrated by
~~al-tabaraani in al-kabeer. see majma’ al-zawaa’id, 3/179; musnad ahmad).
~~these three saheeh ahaadeeth explain the signs which indicate laylat al-
~~qadr. it is not essential for the one who “catches” laylat al-qadr to
~~know that he has “caught” it. the point is to strive hard and to be
~~sincere in worship, whether or not one knows that one has “caught” it.
~~it may be that some of those who do not know that may be better with
~~allaah and higher in status than those who did know which night it was,
