~~take a bath before the eid prayer. the reason why it is mustahabb to
~~take a bath before friday prayer and other public gatherings also
~~applies in the case of eid, only more so. eating before coming out one
~~should not come out to the prayer-place on eid al-fitr before eating
~~some dates, because of the hadeeth narrated by al-bukhaari from anas ibn
~~maalik who said: “the messenger of allaah (peace and blessings of allaah
~~be upon him) would not go out on the morning of eid al-fitr until he had
~~eaten some dates… and he would eat an odd number.” (al-bukhaari, 953) it
~~is mustahabb to eat before coming out because this confirms that we are
~~not allowed to fast on this day, and demonstrates that the fast is now
~~over. ibn hajar (may allaah have mercy on him) explained that this is to
~~prevent people extending the fast and it also means obeying the
~~commandment of allaah. (fath, 2/446). if a person does not have any
~~dates, he can eat anything permissible for breakfast. on eid al-adhaa,
