~~others allowed it. there are reports which indicate that it is
~~permissible to congratulate people on special occasions. the sahaabah
~~used to congratulate one another when something good happened, such as
~~when allaah accepted a person’s repentance and so on. there is no doubt
~~that congratulating others in this way is one of the noblest kinds of
~~good manners and one of the highest social qualities among muslims. at
~~the very least, one can return eid greetings when they are given to you,
~~and remain silent if nothing is said, as imaam ahmad (may allaah have
~~mercy on him) said: “if someone congratulates me, i return the greeting,
~~but i do not initiate it.” looking one’s best for eid PageV42P0019
